AGI - US President Joe Biden asked Iran not to attack Israel: "My message is, "Don't do it." The head of the White House reiterated that the United States is engaged in "the defence of Israel" and that Iran will not succeed".
US President Joe Biden said he was expecting an attack on Iran against Israel quickly. Reprimanded by journalists about how imminent an Iranian retaliation attack against Israel could be, the White House leader said he doesn't want to go into the detail of classified information, but that his expectation is "before rather than after". &nbsp;
In Israel, after about three hours the cabinet of war and internal sources told the country that "there is no need to panic. If Iran attacks, there is a long notice time that will allow to prepare and intercept" missiles.<br> The sources also emphasized that there is "the maximum coordination with Americans: we are in full preparations". The Israeli daily Yedioth Ahronoth.&nbsp reports it;
<h2> Germany invites countrymen to leave Iran
Germany has warned the citizens of leaving Iran, claiming that there is a risk both of sudden escalation of existing tensions between Tehran and Israel. "In current tensions, particularly between Israel and Iran, there is the risk of sudden escalation," writes the Foreign Ministry, in Berlin, in a new travel notice.

