AGI -&nbsp;A Vietnamese real estate magnate was sentenced to death on Thursday in one of the biggest cases of history corruption, with estimated damage in 27 billion dollars>.<br> Truong My Lan, president of the construction giant Van Thinh Phat>, was found guilty of misappropriation of money from Saigon Commercial Bank (SCB) over a decade.
&nbsp;
Eighty-five others, including Lan's husband, grandson and several SCB executives, were convicted by Ho Chi Minh City.<br> Lan's court was born in 1956 in Ho Chi Minh City and her mother had a cosmetics stand on the market. He founded Van Thinh Phat in 1992 and continued to buy luxury hotels, restaurants and apartments, as well as investing in financial services. Many of its real estate projects are located in privileged locations in the centre of Ho Chi Minh City. According to investigators there are more than a thousand companies in the ecosystem > "Van Thinh Phat", including a group of "ghost companies" and a network of interests abroad.
&nbsp;
Lan met Eric Chu Nap Kee, the man destined to become her husband in the early 1990s, while he was looking for investment opportunities. He, a Hong Kong billionaire, was also sentenced to nine years in prison on Thursday. How did you steal so much? Lan was found guilty of three defendants: corruption, violation of banking regulations and undue appropriation. Between 2012 and 2022, he stole $12.5 billion from SCB, submitting false loan requests to withdraw money from the bank, of which he owned a 90% share.
&nbsp;
According to state media, the woman ordered SCB agents to transfer money to convenient companies and then moved the money or picked them up as cash to cover her curses. Between February 2019 and September 2022, his driver transported the equivalent of over $4.4 billion in cash from SCB headquarters in Ho Chi Minh City to his home and headquarters in Van Thinh Phat. Lan also took advantage of a government plan to restructure the SCB to use the bank as a cow to milk after melting with it two other credit institutions. The police have identified more than 40,000 victims of the scam, > all SCB bonders.
<br> Ex employees of the Vietnam State Bank - the central bank - were corrupted with millions of dollars to hide the scarce financial performance of the SCB.
&nbsp;
Do Thi Nhan, the former head of the central bank's inspection team, was sentenced to life for accepting $5.2 million in cash that had been given to her in three boxes of polystyrene. How was she exposed? The operation was led by the powerful secretary-general of the Communist Party Nguyen Phu Trong who from 2021 leads an anti-corruption campaign that led to the incrimination of more than 4,400 people for over 1,700 episodes. But the scope of yesterday's trial has no precedent. The evidence was contained in 104 boxes of the total weight of six tons and involved 200 defense attorneys. The cameras inside the court - which are not always allowed in Vietnam - showed Lan to get agitated and look anxious before the verdict, while many of his co-mates waited with the china head. However, the purge of corruption has caused a severe blow to the economy of Vietnam and analysts claim that some foreign investors have been frightened, although they have widely praised what they see as the goal of the campaign to improve the rule of law.&nbsp;

